An important reminder that with COVID cases on the rise again, it’s imperative we all adhere to the guidelines implemented by NSW Health. 
üì± Book into your classes with your name, phone and email. Classes are restricted to 8-12 people (depending on the class) so if you don’t book you may miss out on a place! We also need record of who attended incase contact tracing is required. 
üèÉüèª‍‚ôÄÔ∏è BYO mat, towel and water with you to the studio. We clean and sanitise between sessions but it really helps us if you can bring your own gear too. 
üí¶ Sanitise your hands with the sanitiser provided when you come into the studio. 
üìè Keep your distance from one another - 1.5m away or 4m square around you. 
ü§í Please stay home if you are sick. We hate missing workouts too but when you’re unwell your body needs to rest. We have many high-risk people visit us weekly, and we want to keep everybody safe. 
To be honest, the first lockdown really hurt us as a small business. It was hard to be positive and we weren’t sure what was going to happen. (We literally found out we had to shut our doors the same day we closed them). So please, let’s all do our bit so we can continue to stay open!
Above all - please stay well and support one another üíõ Sal x

Minyak but-but merupakan salah satu produk HPA yang sangat digemari oleh pengguna. Ini kerana kelebihannya yang pelbagai dalam aspek penjagaan kesihatan. Ia digunakan secara tradisional sebagai minyak sapu atau urut untuk kesakitan anggota badan. Antara kelebihan lain Minyak But-But adalah seperti berikut :-

Untuk urutan - Minyak But-But yang bersifat sejuk di luar dan panas di dalam akan meresap ke dalam lapisan kulit untuk melegakan sakit sendi dan otot. 

Sengatan serangga - Basahi Minyak But-But dengan kapas dan letakkan pada bahagian yang terkena sengatan serangga.

Luka-luka kecil - Ambil kapas dan sapukan pada luka. Jika luka akibat terkena air panas dan luka akibat terbakar, sapukan Minyak But-But ke bahagian yang menggelembung.

Cirit Birit - Minum satu sudu kecil bersama air suam.

Kembung perut - Panaskan sedikit minyak dan sapukan pada bahagian perut. Urut perlahan-lahan secara memutar perlahan-lahan.

Bayi yang sering menangis malam - Sapukan pada bahagian atas kening pada setiap malam.

Kanak-kanak kencing malam - Sapukan pada bahagian ari-ari sebelum tidur.

US economy shrinks at record 32.9% pace in second quarter

Source - Economic Times
Date - 30 July, 2020
Time - 06.21 PM

The¬†US economy¬†suffered its sharpest downturn since at least the 1940s in the second quarter, highlighting how the pandemic has ravaged businesses across the country and left millions of¬†Americans¬†out of work.

Gross domestic product¬†shrank at a 32.9% annualized pace in the second quarter from the first, the most in quarterly records dating back to 1947,¬†the Commerce Department’s initial estimate showed on Thursday. The median forecast in a¬†Bloomberg¬†survey of economists called for a 34.5% slump.

The figures lay bare the extent of the¬†economic devastation¬†that resulted from the government-ordered shutdowns and stay-at-home orders designed to slow the spread of the novel¬†coronavirus¬†that abruptly brought a halt to the longest-running expansion.

Hypothyroidism is a condition in which the thyroid gland does not make enough thyroid hormone. 
As the thyroid hormone is important for growth, repair, and metabolism, people with hypothyroidism may often feel cold and fatigued and may gain weight easily.

Fortunately, you don’t have to avoid many foods if you have hypothyroidism.

You should avoid eating highly processed foods, as they usually contain a lot of calories. This can be a problem if you have hypothyroidism, as you may gain weight easily.

Weight gain is one of the main problems caused by thyroid.

If you are overweight, start losing weight today.

node.text: I’ve been feeling so emotional lately that I don’t even know how to articulate it into words. It’s like I can feel the whole worlds pain weighing on my heart. I can’t categorize my thoughts or my anger because I can’t figure out if I’m just mad about all of the inhumane actions that have taken place? Or if I am mad at everyone who makes selfish decisions in spite of their beliefs? Or when someone chooses politics over someone else’s well being? Or am I just like everyone else who is upset at not just one thing, but every thing. I don’t know. I’m still trying to figure it out. But today I was reminded how thankful I am for my tribe who picks me up when I’m feeling down... and that humanity still exists. #emt #emtlady #firstresponder #eventmedics #covidscreener #maskenthusiast #werq #maskupandshutup #antiracist #blm #blacklivesmatter #justiceforbreonnataylor #socialdistance #essentialworker #fuckyourpoliticalviews #unfollowmeifyoudontlikeit #dont@me #challengeaccepted #fuckthetrend #bebetter

node.text:
We are still in a pandemic. Did you know that if we all wore masks for 4-8 weeks we could knock out this virus and get back on track? The scary part of COVID-19 is the uncertainty. You could have it right now and not know it. It may take a few days or weeks to show symptoms, or you may never have them; and you can easily pass it on to others who will then also unknowingly pass it on, and so on and so forth. Even the healthiest and youngest people can die from COVID-19. I want want us to be able to get back to somewhat normalcy too, but it can’t happen without all of us doing this together. So please, take this seriously. Be considerate of others and do your part by constantly washing your hands and disinfecting frequently touched surfaces, practicing social distancing, and wearing a mask from the moment you leave your home. Thank you. ü¶ãü¶ãü¶ã

Cancelled my trip to Colorado to do my part & stop the spread of COVID-19. I definitely haven’t forgotten there is still a pandemic going on, but I got too comfortable with the small⁣
reprieve from lockdown. However, if you look at the numbers and areas suffering the most, it is clear that we are far from eradicating the virus. üòî⁣
⁣
Be selfless & protect others. Many essential workers are sacrificing for those of us who have the luxury of staying home. Do it for them so that they can go home to their families, safe & healthy. ‚ù£Ô∏è⁣
⁣
I personally am going to be reverting back to my stricter happy @ home norm to do my part. I am going to embrace my 640 square feet & my cuddle bunny. I will see my favorite humans on video chat & be leaving my home for socially distant activities like runs, walks, paddle boarding, or hiking. Any other adventures will be essential trips. ⁣
⁣
My To Do List:⁣
1. Work üíº ⁣
2. Workout üèÉüèª‍‚ôÄÔ∏è ⁣
3. Plan video catch ups üé• ⁣

node.text:
SLEEPER OF THE WEEK: Allen Lazard

Allen Lazard appeared in all 16 games last year but had only three starts. All of his stats were accumulated in the final 11 weeks (weeks 6-17). He finished with
Lazard was only behind superstar Devante Adams in receiving yard with 477 of his own. Lazard was targeted at least three times from week 9 on throughout the season. He is a big bodied (6’5), rangy receiver with great hands and boasts 4.5 speed. He will get plenty of one on one opportunities with Adams commanding so much attention. 
We have to believe that the coaching staff believes in his abilities, as everyone anticipated the Packers to give Aaron Rodgers help in this past draft. The Packers went a route none of us expected, and didn’t add anyone to the WR room. 
The way Lazard came up big down the stretch for Green Bay bodes well for the 2020 season. Rodgers and Lazard connected in some key moments in the forth quarter. There have been rumblings from the Packers front office about moving him to TE, but they like him enough where he is to make that change. He can easily beat out Allison and Valdez-Scantling for the No. 2 WR spot in Green Bay.

node.text:
The coronavirus pandemic will never end because there are far more desperate, ignorant, unruly and risky individuals that think they are invincible and immune to this virus.

This pandemic of our lifetime the Coronavirus will only end when they find a vaccine to treat it or kill it.

This bleared photo show crowds of people at the Upper Marlboro Pool Party at the Broadwater Estate off of Crain Highway in Upper Marlboro, Maryland, where police were dispersed to end the party two different times on Saturday.

I'm certain there are more videos and photographs online of this event at the Broadwater Estate in Upper Marlboro, Maryland.

Mind you, these people are going back home to someone, around others and communities, whether it's work, relationships, friendships, caregivers, children, family members and other situations.

A witness that lives in the area said, "There were a million and one cars parked on the highway," resident Bianca Mitchell told News4.

I get it. People can do whatever they desire.

But it is extremely concerned and sobering how desperate some people are to get out, take a picture or video to say they did something with the potential risk with one of the most deadly and infectious pandemic ever.

The numbers are surging with people still getting infected and dying and you can't advise people reasonably about the sickness,  death and long-term consequences of this virus.

You can't talk to them because they have an answer for every reason they're doing, what they're doing.ü§î

God bless them all, that they never catch the coronavirus or effect anybody else.üôè
